          "sql_elevated_roles",
          "mongo_exercised_perms"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "cost_rationale": "Three subtasks with minimal decomposition: (1) sql_gen (mid) retrieves elevated role grants from relational IAM system\u2014requires multi-table joins across role, permission, and grant tables. (2) mongo_query (mid) aggregates audit events across 180 days, grouped by role and permission\u2014standard aggregation pipeline. (3) cross_recon (frontier) reconciles two data sources, performs set difference logic to identify never-used permissions, classifies each grant by usage pattern, and generates revocation candidates with contextual confidence\u2014requires high capability for multi-signal reconciliation and classification decision-making. This is a single-pass enterprise-wide compliance assessment with no need for policy_action (compliance flagging is part of cross_recon's reconciliation output)."
